And we'll go through
them throughout the day

00:04:20.920 --> 00:04:21.960
in more details.

00:04:27.910 --> 00:04:32.520
So importantly, your
game is the key, right?

00:04:32.520 --> 00:04:34.980
You are doing great
at developing games,

00:04:34.980 --> 00:04:37.700
and that's the most
important thing that matters.

00:04:37.700 --> 00:04:41.145
But the world has become
quite complicated.

00:04:41.145 --> 00:04:42.520
There are so many
things that you

00:04:42.520 --> 00:04:46.285
need to consider on top of
actually making a great game.

00:04:46.285 --> 00:04:51.040
You need to ask yourself, how
do I make the infrastructure so

00:04:51.040 --> 00:04:55.170
that it scales with your game
as it becomes more popular?

00:04:55.170 --> 00:04:57.950
How do you actually
distribute your game, so

00:04:57.950 --> 00:05:01.070
that you get millions
of users using it?

00:05:01.070 --> 00:05:03.340
Once you have the
users in your system,

00:05:03.340 --> 00:05:05.880
how do you engage the
users more deeply?

00:05:05.880 --> 00:05:07.842
And last but not
least, you might

00:05:07.842 --> 00:05:09.300
want to make a lot
of money with it

00:05:09.300 --> 00:05:13.690
as well, so you can pay
your development team.

00:05:13.690 --> 00:05:16.520
And so you need to find
the right systems in place

00:05:16.520 --> 00:05:18.130
so you can monetize well.

00:05:18.130 --> 00:05:22.060
And what I want to do today
is give you a brief tour,

00:05:22.060 --> 00:05:23.850
running through
the Google services

00:05:23.850 --> 00:05:26.690
on how they can help you
with those specific points.

00:05:32.620 --> 00:05:37.000
So let's start with
taking the work away

00:05:37.000 --> 00:05:43.920
on the infrastructure, to
make your games scalable.

00:05:43.920 --> 00:05:46.665
You might have heard of this
operating system, Android,

00:05:46.665 --> 00:05:47.165
before.

00:05:49.670 --> 00:05:52.280
So clearly, we are
putting a lot of effort

00:05:52.280 --> 00:05:57.330
in developing the
SDK, making it work on

00:05:57.330 --> 00:05:59.490
as many devices as possible.

00:05:59.490 --> 00:06:03.090
Android 4.4 KitKat has
been out for some time.

00:06:03.090 --> 00:06:05.090
So I'm sure you're
all familiar with it.

00:06:05.090 --> 00:06:08.970
But with this release, I feel
we've taken it another level,

00:06:08.970 --> 00:06:11.405
making it available
on even more devices.

00:06:14.950 --> 00:06:17.950
We would encourage you to
develop natively on the SDK,

00:06:17.950 --> 00:06:20.550
to really benefit
from the efficiency

00:06:20.550 --> 00:06:23.840
and the responsiveness that
you can get on those devices.

00:06:23.840 --> 00:06:26.540
And of course, we also
have put in a lot of effort

00:06:26.540 --> 00:06:31.020
on the developer support so that
you can code, debug, and test.

00:06:36.220 --> 00:06:41.135
On the Google Play Games,
this is a great piece

00:06:41.135 --> 00:06:44.880
of infrastructure, so that a
number of real life problems

00:06:44.880 --> 00:06:46.630
that you have, or that
you should consider

00:06:46.630 --> 00:06:48.600
to make your games
more interesting--

00:06:48.600 --> 00:06:53.130
such as multiplayer support,
or keeping scores, et cetera--

00:06:53.130 --> 00:06:57.170
that this level of services
can take care of it

00:06:57.170 --> 00:07:00.330
so you can focus on the
core aspect of your game.

00:07:00.330 --> 00:07:03.350
And clearly we heard
you, that if you really

00:07:03.350 --> 00:07:05.200
want to support
multiplayer games,

00:07:05.200 --> 00:07:09.820
it needs to be available
across operating systems.

00:07:09.820 --> 00:07:11.970
And I believe that was
one of the announcements,

00:07:11.970 --> 00:07:16.000
that it's not only Android,
but also iOS and support also

00:07:16.000 --> 00:07:16.550
for web.

00:07:19.080 --> 00:07:21.250
Cloud Save has been
out for some time.

00:07:21.250 --> 00:07:24.170
But let me share one of the
frustrations that I have,

00:07:24.170 --> 00:07:25.820
as a gamer.

00:07:25.820 --> 00:07:30.760
Like many people in the room,
I have multiple devices.

00:07:30.760 --> 00:07:33.120
You've probably all
seen this chart,

00:07:33.120 --> 00:07:35.780
that you start in the morning
with your mobile phone.

00:07:35.780 --> 00:07:36.970
You commute to work.

00:07:36.970 --> 00:07:40.000
Then during the day, you
use your laptop, desktop

00:07:40.000 --> 00:07:40.960
more heavily.

00:07:40.960 --> 00:07:41.894
Then you commute back.

00:07:41.894 --> 00:07:44.560
You use your phone, and then you
use your tablet in the evening.

00:07:44.560 --> 00:07:45.650
A lot of people do that.

00:07:45.650 --> 00:07:48.450
It's not just me
who's doing that.

00:07:48.450 --> 00:07:51.520
So I find it very frustrating
that when I'm at home

00:07:51.520 --> 00:07:54.690
and I want to use the laptop
I can't play any of the games.

00:07:54.690 --> 00:07:56.960
Because a lot of
you still force me,

00:07:56.960 --> 00:07:58.530
that if I start
playing your games

00:07:58.530 --> 00:08:01.150
I have to start from scratch.

00:08:01.150 --> 00:08:04.080
I spent so much time and
effort to go up to this level,

00:08:04.080 --> 00:08:05.540
and of course when
I switch device,

00:08:05.540 --> 00:08:07.440
I want to continue
with that level.

00:08:07.440 --> 00:08:11.520
So please, just for me,
please develop your games so

00:08:11.520 --> 00:08:15.500
that you save the score
and the level somewhere.

00:08:15.500 --> 00:08:17.880
I think that the Google
Play Games service

00:08:17.880 --> 00:08:21.070
is a great and
easy way to do it.

00:08:21.070 --> 00:08:24.050
But if you want to do it another
way, just please do it for me.

00:08:27.900 --> 00:08:31.680
And of course it's
not only mobile,

00:08:31.680 --> 00:08:33.460
but we also have a
great set of tools

00:08:33.460 --> 00:08:34.809
that helps you on the web.

00:08:34.809 --> 00:08:39.780
So specifically, we
have a set of APIs

00:08:39.780 --> 00:08:42.580
as part of the Chrome packaged
apps, that really allow you

00:08:42.580 --> 00:08:48.910
to have web-based games
using HTML, JavaScript, CSS,

00:08:48.910 --> 00:08:52.960
so that you can create the same
experience-- so that they're

00:08:52.960 --> 00:08:56.920
as powerful as a native app, but
they're as safe as a web app.

00:09:00.230 --> 00:09:05.560
It's not just
user-facing technology.

00:09:05.560 --> 00:09:07.770
A lot of things need to go
in the background as well,

00:09:07.770 --> 00:09:12.450
to make your game scalable so
that when it really takes off,

00:09:12.450 --> 00:09:13.330
your game works.

00:09:13.330 --> 00:09:16.360
And what we have done is--
exactly the same technology

00:09:16.360 --> 00:09:20.200
that we use at Google to
make our system scalable--

00:09:20.200 --> 00:09:24.410
we make that available to you
as a Google Cloud Platform

00:09:24.410 --> 00:09:25.760
service.

00:09:25.760 --> 00:09:29.660
I actually look forward to
the session later from Kaj

00:09:29.660 --> 00:09:31.830
from MAG Interactive,
who's going

00:09:31.830 --> 00:09:34.690
to share his experience of
how this is working for him.

00:09:40.560 --> 00:09:44.190
So I hope that has
given you some ideas.

00:09:44.190 --> 00:09:47.350
I'm sure you know some
of these weren't exactly

00:09:47.350 --> 00:09:50.930
new things, of what services you
can use from Google that helps

00:09:50.930 --> 00:09:54.810
you with the
infrastructure aspect.

00:09:54.810 --> 00:09:57.050
But of course, you
want to get to users.

00:09:57.050 --> 00:09:58.500
You want to get
millions of users.

00:09:58.500 --> 00:10:00.630
You want to get hundreds
of millions of users.

00:10:00.630 --> 00:10:03.670
So let's go through, what are
the tools that we can help you

00:10:03.670 --> 00:10:04.700
with that challenge.

00:10:07.630 --> 00:10:11.100
The first one is
again an obvious one,

00:10:11.100 --> 00:10:15.580
and Dan will speak to that in
more detail, of how you really

00:10:15.580 --> 00:10:18.600
get the best out of the
Google Play Platform

00:10:18.600 --> 00:10:19.930
to distribute the game.

00:10:19.930 --> 00:10:21.870
But the numbers
speak for themselves.

00:10:21.870 --> 00:10:23.870
50 billion downloaded apps.

00:10:23.870 --> 00:10:26.420
Another 2 billion every month.

00:10:26.420 --> 00:10:28.720
Clearly, this is something
to look into, and really

00:10:28.720 --> 00:10:30.850
optimize for you.

00:10:35.360 --> 00:10:37.940
Just as we had before,
don't forget the web.

00:10:40.900 --> 00:10:43.880
The Chrome store is
really a fantastic way

00:10:43.880 --> 00:10:47.680
to distribute web
versions of your game.

00:10:47.680 --> 00:10:51.390
And it has hundreds
of millions of users.

00:10:51.390 --> 00:10:54.530
It is an opportunity that you
should definitely think about.

00:10:57.940 --> 00:10:59.910
And I have a surprise for you.

00:10:59.910 --> 00:11:01.930
Advertising actually does work.

00:11:05.500 --> 00:11:08.340
Obviously, people
will use your game,

00:11:08.340 --> 00:11:10.110
ultimately because
it's a great game.

00:11:10.110 --> 00:11:13.870
If you have a game that's not so
great, no level of advertising

00:11:13.870 --> 00:11:15.190
is gonna help with that.

00:11:15.190 --> 00:11:18.150
But what you can do is
just to get more users

00:11:18.150 --> 00:11:19.750
to actually discover your game.

00:11:19.750 --> 00:11:23.680
So whether it's-- which
this screen is depicting--

00:11:23.680 --> 00:11:26.890
whether it's a focused
text search campaign--

00:11:26.890 --> 00:11:28.790
so if a user is
searching for your game,

00:11:28.790 --> 00:11:31.030
or is searching for
something very similar,

00:11:31.030 --> 00:11:33.150
that you direct
them to your game.

00:11:33.150 --> 00:11:36.020
Or whether it's a
re-marketing campaign

00:11:36.020 --> 00:11:38.790
that you have a user who
has played very frequently,

00:11:38.790 --> 00:11:42.130
and somehow they have stopped,
to remind them about it.

00:11:42.130 --> 00:11:45.530
Or a re-marketing campaign,
because you have now a game

00:11:45.530 --> 00:11:47.740
that you think would
interest the same user.

00:11:47.740 --> 00:11:49.760
Or you want to
attract completely

00:11:49.760 --> 00:11:56.020
new people, new players, and you
use more rich engagement ads.

00:11:56.020 --> 00:11:58.610
Either videos or
display ads, so that

00:11:58.610 --> 00:12:02.760
you can really tell the story of
the visual appeal of the game,

00:12:02.760 --> 00:12:06.090
and create that experience.

00:12:06.090 --> 00:12:07.390
It definitely does work.

00:12:11.920 --> 00:12:17.450
Now once you start
paying for users,

00:12:17.450 --> 00:12:19.546
you have to look
into metrics that you

00:12:19.546 --> 00:12:20.545
spend your money wisely.

00:12:23.950 --> 00:12:26.510
The cost of user acquisition
is not necessarily

00:12:26.510 --> 00:12:28.520
the most important aspect.

00:12:28.520 --> 00:12:31.490
So let's just assume
that the game that you

00:12:31.490 --> 00:12:33.750
want to distribute is
actually a free game,

00:12:33.750 --> 00:12:36.100
and you want to make money
through in-app purchases

00:12:36.100 --> 00:12:37.490
or through advertising.

00:12:37.490 --> 00:12:41.340
So no matter what you
have spent to acquire

00:12:41.340 --> 00:12:45.420
that particular user, if that
user only downloads the game

00:12:45.420 --> 00:12:46.950
and doesn't actually
play it, that

00:12:46.950 --> 00:12:48.900
was not a very smart investment.

00:12:48.900 --> 00:12:51.880
And so really look
for-- is that you

00:12:51.880 --> 00:12:54.200
need the deep analytics
to figure out,

00:12:54.200 --> 00:12:56.160
how do you get the
return on you investment?

00:12:56.160 --> 00:12:58.860
How would you get that user
who was actually making

00:12:58.860 --> 00:13:01.430
the purchase, is making
the in-app purchase,

00:13:01.430 --> 00:13:03.910
or is playing the
game long enough so

00:13:03.910 --> 00:13:06.510
that you can show them enough
ads that it actually pays off

00:13:06.510 --> 00:13:09.030
for you.

00:13:09.030 --> 00:13:12.850
One of the great things where
our product suite really helps

00:13:12.850 --> 00:13:17.060
you, is that we now have very
deep integration between AdMob

00:13:17.060 --> 00:13:20.950
and analytics, so you can easily
see that segmentation to really

00:13:20.950 --> 00:13:24.256
understand which campaign
is working for you and which

00:13:24.256 --> 00:13:24.755
isn't.

00:13:32.690 --> 00:13:34.400
So now we're in a good state.

00:13:34.400 --> 00:13:37.950
You have hundreds of
millions of users.

00:13:37.950 --> 00:13:40.000
Clearly they will
stay in your game,

00:13:40.000 --> 00:13:41.810
because it's a great
game experience.

00:13:41.810 --> 00:13:45.890
But what other services
can Google help you with,

00:13:45.890 --> 00:13:48.230
just to deepen the
engagement even further?

00:13:51.310 --> 00:13:55.710
First one-- and we'll hear
about that later today as well--

00:13:55.710 --> 00:14:00.010
I think it's the next
session, actually--

00:14:00.010 --> 00:14:01.710
on how to have
multiplayer support.

00:14:01.710 --> 00:14:03.180
I won't go too much into detail.

00:14:03.180 --> 00:14:07.360
But in essence, the more
you can get your users

00:14:07.360 --> 00:14:10.120
to play with their friends,
play against their friends,

00:14:10.120 --> 00:14:13.190
share things with their friends,
the more they are delighted,

00:14:13.190 --> 00:14:15.620
and the better the
experience is for them.

00:14:15.620 --> 00:14:18.327
And this is a solution that
we make available to you

00:14:18.327 --> 00:14:20.410
so you don't have to do a
lot of coding around it.

00:14:23.130 --> 00:14:25.620
Of course the same
is true for the web.

00:14:25.620 --> 00:14:29.930
And I just wanted to point
out-- one thing that I get a lot

00:14:29.930 --> 00:14:32.510
of positive feedback from
publishers who have a strong

00:14:32.510 --> 00:14:37.890
web presence, is that if you use
the Google+ sign-in process--

00:14:37.890 --> 00:14:40.780
similar to Google Play that
you can purchase something

00:14:40.780 --> 00:14:43.670
on the web and it gets
downloaded to your Android

00:14:43.670 --> 00:14:48.290
device-- when a user logs in on
your service using the Google+

00:14:48.290 --> 00:14:52.690
functionality, you have the
ability to directly download

00:14:52.690 --> 00:14:56.850
and install the mobile app that
you want on the user's devices.

00:14:56.850 --> 00:14:59.480
So I think that's
another great way

00:14:59.480 --> 00:15:05.770
how to distribute
your applications

00:15:05.770 --> 00:15:09.280
Let's see how well
you know your YouTube.

00:15:09.280 --> 00:15:11.990
And anyone from Google
is not allowed to answer.

00:15:11.990 --> 00:15:16.040
Who knows what is the most
