AUDIENCE: Probably PewDiePie.

00:15:21.700 --> 00:15:23.890
THOMAS SCHREIBER: Exactly.

00:15:23.890 --> 00:15:26.440
He's got 25 million subscribers.

00:15:26.440 --> 00:15:27.290
And it's incredible.

00:15:27.290 --> 00:15:29.790
If you think about all the
content, all the videos, all

00:15:29.790 --> 00:15:32.240
the channels, it's
actually the gaming sector

00:15:32.240 --> 00:15:35.440
that is the number one.

00:15:35.440 --> 00:15:40.160
I think this is an area that
is almost like a hidden secret.

00:15:40.160 --> 00:15:42.300
And more can be made of it.

00:15:42.300 --> 00:15:45.780
Gaming content is
incredibly popular on video.

00:15:45.780 --> 00:15:48.450
And Ibrahim will go
into more details later.

00:15:48.450 --> 00:15:50.440
But because it is
like that, it's

00:15:50.440 --> 00:15:53.370
good to think-- to both use
it as a promotional tool

00:15:53.370 --> 00:15:56.070
to show the power of your
games, the experience

00:15:56.070 --> 00:15:57.900
that people have--
but also think

00:15:57.900 --> 00:16:01.550
about in your games,
either using video actually

00:16:01.550 --> 00:16:05.960
in the games, or if someone has
had a nice gaming experience

00:16:05.960 --> 00:16:08.852
can you use, for
example, YouTube APIs,

00:16:08.852 --> 00:16:11.435
that they can share that gaming
experience with their friends.

00:16:17.130 --> 00:16:20.600
And then obviously, you want
to listen to your users.

00:16:24.000 --> 00:16:27.170
You want to have a game
where the comments they give,

00:16:27.170 --> 00:16:28.920
the ratings they give is high.

00:16:28.920 --> 00:16:32.510
If you have high ratings,
your ranking is higher,

00:16:32.510 --> 00:16:37.020
you get more users, you make
more money, life is good.

00:16:37.020 --> 00:16:40.810
And we have a mechanism
to give that feedback.

00:16:40.810 --> 00:16:42.670
So focusing on
quality is important.

00:16:42.670 --> 00:16:45.770
At the same time,
what is crucial

00:16:45.770 --> 00:16:48.100
is don't just put out
your game and then

00:16:48.100 --> 00:16:50.690
hope that users will love it.

00:16:50.690 --> 00:16:52.320
Because the reverse
can also happen.

00:16:52.320 --> 00:16:55.040
That if users aren't happy
they give you bad ratings,

00:16:55.040 --> 00:16:57.110
and then everything
spirals down.

00:16:57.110 --> 00:17:01.120
So what we would recommend is
that you use the alpha and beta

00:17:01.120 --> 00:17:03.150
testing tool that we have.

00:17:03.150 --> 00:17:07.440
So you can test it out with
a trusted group of gamers.

00:17:07.440 --> 00:17:10.339
And they will give
you the feedback.

00:17:10.339 --> 00:17:12.640
And then in a dialogue
you can improve your game.

00:17:12.640 --> 00:17:15.839
And only when you know you are
really ready you push it out,

00:17:15.839 --> 00:17:17.659
and you got much more success.

00:17:21.579 --> 00:17:22.079
Right.

00:17:22.079 --> 00:17:26.390
So now we come to last section.

00:17:26.390 --> 00:17:28.339
You have a scalable game.

00:17:28.339 --> 00:17:30.490
You have reached lots of users.

00:17:30.490 --> 00:17:32.430
They stay even more
engaged with the game,

00:17:32.430 --> 00:17:35.470
spending more time because
of all the social features--

00:17:35.470 --> 00:17:36.910
YouTube engagement, et cetera.

00:17:36.910 --> 00:17:40.320
But I guess most of you actually
want to make money out of it.

00:17:43.780 --> 00:17:47.230
The obvious, and very,
very important mechanism,

00:17:47.230 --> 00:17:48.840
is of course to sell your game.

00:17:48.840 --> 00:17:53.580
And with Google Play
supporting to sell your game

00:17:53.580 --> 00:17:58.310
in over 130 countries, that's
of course a great opportunity

00:17:58.310 --> 00:17:59.790
how to make money.

00:17:59.790 --> 00:18:04.010
But life is more complicated.

00:18:04.010 --> 00:18:06.270
Clearly, this is a
fantastic revenue stream,

00:18:06.270 --> 00:18:12.480
how to sell money-- not
selling money, making money.

00:18:12.480 --> 00:18:14.830
But the sad truth
is that when you

00:18:14.830 --> 00:18:17.340
look behind the
actual numbers, it's

00:18:17.340 --> 00:18:19.320
a very, very small
percentage of users

00:18:19.320 --> 00:18:22.950
who are willing to pay
money for your games.

00:18:22.950 --> 00:18:24.880
A recent study that
I have read claimed

00:18:24.880 --> 00:18:28.920
that the majority of revenue
made from in-app purchases

00:18:28.920 --> 00:18:33.090
or from up-front purchases
is less than 0.2 percent

00:18:33.090 --> 00:18:34.500
of your users.

00:18:34.500 --> 00:18:38.230
So if that is the case, then you
should ask yourself, well what

00:18:38.230 --> 00:18:41.160
about the other 99.8
percent of the users.

00:18:41.160 --> 00:18:44.690
Are you OK to not make
any money out of them?

00:18:44.690 --> 00:18:48.570
Personally how I think
about this challenge is,

00:18:48.570 --> 00:18:51.660
I think it's less a question
whether you personally

00:18:51.660 --> 00:18:54.620
think ads are a
great thing or not.

00:18:54.620 --> 00:18:55.950
But users have a preference.

00:18:55.950 --> 00:18:59.790
So some users are willing to
pay money to get an experience,

00:18:59.790 --> 00:19:00.640
and some are not.

00:19:00.640 --> 00:19:03.240
And for those who are not
prepared to make money

00:19:03.240 --> 00:19:06.180
advertising, I think is
a very legitimate way

00:19:06.180 --> 00:19:08.350
for you to make money
for all the hard work

00:19:08.350 --> 00:19:10.280
that you have done.

00:19:10.280 --> 00:19:14.140
And actually, we have
worked very hard on this.

00:19:14.140 --> 00:19:18.820
I think it would be fair to
say that two years ago, AdMob

00:19:18.820 --> 00:19:24.690
was merely a demand platform,
that we help you to get ads.

00:19:24.690 --> 00:19:27.630
But it has grown tremendously.

00:19:27.630 --> 00:19:33.490
It is now a fully working
advertising solution,

00:19:33.490 --> 00:19:36.920
in that it's deeply
integrated with Google Play.

00:19:36.920 --> 00:19:40.360
So for example, if
you want, at run time,

00:19:40.360 --> 00:19:45.720
to figure out, should I actually
have an in-app purchase ad,

00:19:45.720 --> 00:19:48.140
then we have that
integration and it

00:19:48.140 --> 00:19:50.700
puts you directly
to the Play Store.

00:19:50.700 --> 00:19:53.060
It also is deeply
integrated into analytics,

00:19:53.060 --> 00:19:54.060
which is very important.

00:19:54.060 --> 00:19:56.810
Because those users who
pay you a lot of money--

00:19:56.810 --> 00:19:58.770
well maybe, even
though you love ads,

00:19:58.770 --> 00:20:00.690
you may not want to
show them any ads.

00:20:00.690 --> 00:20:03.340
And you need exactly
that segmentation--

00:20:03.340 --> 00:20:09.970
getting all the signals out of
your application from analytics

00:20:09.970 --> 00:20:11.910
all combined, so
that you can dice

00:20:11.910 --> 00:20:14.390
and slice the user
to really give--

00:20:14.390 --> 00:20:17.890
to really use the optimal
monetize strategy.

00:20:17.890 --> 00:20:20.080
Now clearly, you are in control.

00:20:20.080 --> 00:20:25.110
But get the most out
of this opportunity.

00:20:25.110 --> 00:20:27.430
So this is one way how to do it.

00:20:27.430 --> 00:20:30.840
For those users who don't
want to pay for your app,

00:20:30.840 --> 00:20:32.050
you can have a display ad.

00:20:32.050 --> 00:20:36.860
But of course that's not
the only thing how to do it.

00:20:36.860 --> 00:20:39.260
I think another
great way how to do

00:20:39.260 --> 00:20:40.890
it is to have more
engaging formats.

00:20:40.890 --> 00:20:44.230
And I think the skippable
ad format that we provide,

00:20:44.230 --> 00:20:47.280
I think is actually another
fantastic mechanism.

00:20:47.280 --> 00:20:50.810
So let's say-- clearly not
in the middle of the game,

00:20:50.810 --> 00:20:55.340
but once the user has
reached a certain level--

00:20:55.340 --> 00:20:58.480
and it's the kind of user who's
not giving you money anyway--

00:20:58.480 --> 00:21:00.670
why don't you show
them a skippable ad?

00:21:00.670 --> 00:21:02.850
And then the user has a choice.

00:21:02.850 --> 00:21:05.690
They can either skip the ad,
and continue playing your game.

00:21:05.690 --> 00:21:08.590
And that's fine, because they're
not interested to see the ad.

00:21:08.590 --> 00:21:12.310
And so the value to the
advertiser's also not so great.

00:21:12.310 --> 00:21:15.460
Because they want the audience
to engage with their ad.

00:21:15.460 --> 00:21:18.740
Or, they actually decide
that they want to see the ad,

00:21:18.740 --> 00:21:20.880
and then it's fantastic
for the advertisers

00:21:20.880 --> 00:21:23.720
and they're willing to pay
a lot of money for that.

00:21:23.720 --> 00:21:26.280
And so this is the
experience that we provide.

00:21:29.940 --> 00:21:35.320
I just wanted to mention, given
that at Google the majority

00:21:35.320 --> 00:21:37.540
of revenue comes
from advertising,

00:21:37.540 --> 00:21:39.650
clearly this is our
bread and butter.

00:21:39.650 --> 00:21:41.750
And the tools that
we use internally,

00:21:41.750 --> 00:21:44.270
we also make available to you.

00:21:44.270 --> 00:21:49.160
So if you are a very
large games company,

00:21:49.160 --> 00:21:51.290
and you have your
own sales force that

00:21:51.290 --> 00:21:53.680
goes out in the market
and sells it directly,

00:21:53.680 --> 00:21:58.840
obviously we can offer
you the same tools

00:21:58.840 --> 00:22:01.100
that any big company
uses to really make

00:22:01.100 --> 00:22:02.310
that a scalable process.

00:22:02.310 --> 00:22:03.880
And it's all fully integrated.

00:22:03.880 --> 00:22:07.190
So it works with AdMob
and it works with video,

00:22:07.190 --> 00:22:10.170
and it works across
all platforms,

00:22:10.170 --> 00:22:12.740
and it's all the same system.

00:22:12.740 --> 00:22:16.730
And I even take a personal bet
that no matter what advertising

00:22:16.730 --> 00:22:21.590
solution you have-- because
of all this deep integration--

00:22:21.590 --> 00:22:24.240
I would take a personal bet
that we would generate more

00:22:24.240 --> 00:22:25.970
revenue than any other system.

